<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/387.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following was telegraphed to Consul, Tampico, on August 4: [Quotes
                            telegram of August 4, 1914, to Vice Consul Bevan.]</p>
                        <p>Consul has replied as follows: [Quotes telegram of August 6, 1914, from
                            Vice Consul Bevan.]</p>
                        <p>Bring this matter most forcibly to General Carranza’s attention and urge
                            that the decrees providing for unjust levies of taxes at Tampico be
                            withdrawn, as they appear to be excessive and discriminatory and will
                            result in closing down industrial institutions and thus be injurious to
                            the welfare of Mexico. Request him to telegraph adequate order to
                            Nafarrate,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>